line_1: These aged knees — my soul yet feels their grasp!
line_2: Then parting, at my feet they bend, and clasp

line_1: Thy arms, the air-drawn charmer, never grasp.

line_2: To all in life its love would clasp
I live within my arms to clasp,

line_1: To-morrow, chill'd by death's cold grasp,
line_2: This hand no longer thine shall clasp;

line_1: He struggles from the stranger's grasp:
line_2: His little arms his mother clasp.
